Sure, here's a simple example of how to add a button that opens up the camera in a React Native (iOS) app.

First, make sure you install the camera package if you haven't already:

```sh
npm install expo-camera
```

Then, you'll need to request permission to access the camera, and then you can create a button to open the camera. The full code would look something like this:

1. First, let's set up the necessary imports and state in your component:

```jsx
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import { StyleSheet, View, Button, Platform } from 'react-native';
import * as Permissions from 'expo-permissions';
import * as Camera roll from 'expo-camera';

const App = () => {
  const [hasPermission, setHasPermission] = useState(null);
  const [cameraRef, setCameraRef] = useState(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    (async () => {
      if (Platform.OS === 'ios') {
        const permission = await Permissions.askAsync(Permissions.CAMERA);
        setHasPermission(permission);
      }
    })();
  }, []);

  const handlePress = () => {
    if (cameraRef) {
      cameraRef.takePictureAsync();
    }
  };

  return (
    <View style={styles.container}>
      {hasPermission !== null ? (
        <Camera ref={setCameraRef} style={styles.camera}>
          { /* you can add content between the view tags to appear on top of the camera preview */ }
        </Camera>
      ) : (
        <View style={styles.noPermission}>
          <Text style={styles.noPermissionText}>Camera permission is required</Text>
        </View>
      )}

      <Button title="Open Camera" onPress={handlePress} />
    </View>
  );
};

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: {
    flex: 1,
    flexDirection: 'row',
    alignItems: 'center',
    justifyContent: 'center',
  },
  noPermission: {
    alignItems: 'center',
    marginTop: 30,
  },
  noPermissionText: {
    alignSelf: 'center',
  },
});

export default App;
```

This sets up a simple UI with a button to open the camera when permission is granted, and show a text message if the permission hasn't been granted yet.

Make sure that you handle the returned value from the permission prompt correctly, and also remember to ask for permissions again if they were denied upon app launch.

