To integrate Wistia Uploader into your Angular 14 project, you'll need to follow these general steps:

1. **Install the Wistia Uploader library:**
   Wistia Uploader is a simple and intuitive library to handle file uploads in Angular applications. While there isn't a pre-built Angular library, you can use Wistia API directly within Angular components.

2. **Set up a new Angular project:**
   First, ensure you have Angular CLI installed. If not, install it by running:
   ```sh
   npm install -g @angular/cli
   ```
   Create a new Angular 14 project:
   ```sh
   ng new angular-wistia-uploader
   cd angular-wistia-uploader
   ```

3. **Install necessary dependencies:**
   Although there's no specific npm package for Wistia Uploader, you will create a simple utility to interact with Wistia's API. Angular Material and NgxHttpClient are useful for handling HTTP requests.

4. **Create a new component:**
   Generate a new component for the upload feature:
   ```sh
   ng generate component WistiaUpload
   ```

5. **Edit the service to upload files to Wistia:**
   Create a service to handle the upload process:
   ```sh
   ng generate service wistia-upload
   ```
   Edit the `wistia-upload.service.ts` file:
   ```typescript
   import { Injectable } from '@angular/core';
   import { HttpClient, HttpEvent, HttpEventType, HttpRequest } from '@angular/common/http';
   import { Observable } from 'rxjs';
   import { tap } from 'rxjs/operators';

   @Injectable({
     providedIn: 'root'
   })
   export class WistiaUploadService {
     private readonly WISTIA_UPLOAD_URL = 'https://upload.wistia.com'; // Wistia upload URL, change accordingly

     constructor(private http: HttpClient) {}

     public uploadVideo(file: File): Observable<any> {
       const formData: FormData = new FormData();
       formData.append('file', file, file.name);

       const httpRequest = new HttpRequest('POST', `${this.WISTIA_UPLOAD_URL}/video/upload`, formData);
       return this.http.request(httpRequest).pipe(
         tap(evt => {
           if (evt.type === HttpEventType.Response) {
             console.log('Upload complete:', evt.body);
           }
         })
       );
     }
   }
   ```

6. **Update the component:**
   Modify `wistia-upload.component.ts` to handle the upload logic:
   ```typescript
   import { Component } from '@angular/core';
   import { WistiaUploadService } from './wistia-upload.service';

   @Component({
     selector: 'app-wistia-upload',
     templateUrl: './wistia-upload.component.html',
     styleUrls: ['./wistia-upload.component.css']
   })
   export class WistiaUploadComponent {
     selectedFile: File;

     constructor(private wistiaUploadService: WistiaUploadService) {}

     onFileSelected(event: any) {
       this.selectedFile = (<FileList>event.target)[0];
     }

     onUpload() {
       if (this.selectedFile) {
         this.wistiaUploadService.uploadVideo(this.selectedFile).subscribe({
           next: (response) => {
             console.log('Video uploaded:', response);
           },
           error: (error) => {
             console.error('Failed to upload video:', error);
           }
         });
       } else {
         console.log('No file selected');
       }
     }
   }
   ```

7. **Modify the component's template:**
   Edit `wistia-upload.component.html` to include a file input and an upload button:
   ```html
   <div>
     <input type="file" (change)="onFileSelected($event)" multiple>
     <button (click)="onUpload()" [disabled]="!selectedFile">Upload Video</button>
   </div>
   ```

8. **Update app.module.ts:**
   Ensure you import the necessary modules, including NgxHttpClientModule:
   ```typescript
   import { NgModule } from '@angular/core';
   import { BrowserModule } from '@angular/platform-browser';
   import { HttpClientModule } from '@angular/common/http';
   import { FormsModule } from '@angular/forms';
   import { AppComponent } from './app.component';
   import { WistiaUploadComponent } from './wistia-upload/wistia-upload.component';

   @NgModule({
     declarations: [
       AppComponent,
       WistiaUploadComponent
     ],
     imports: [
       BrowserModule,
       HttpClientModule,
       FormsModule
     ],
     providers: [],
     bootstrap: [AppComponent]
   })
   export class AppModule { }
   ```

9. **Run your Angular application:**
   `ng serve`

