To create a browser extension that links strings matching Tezos wallet or contract addresses to tzkt.io, you'll need to follow several steps. I’ll guide you through the creation of the extension, including the necessary files and basic functionalities.

1. **Setting Up the Manifest File (manifest.json)**

```json
{
  "manifest_version": 3,
  "name": "Tezos Address Linker",
  "version": "1.0",
  "description": "Link Tezos wallet and contract addresses to tzkt.io",
  "permissions": ["activeTab", "storage"],
  "background": {
    "service_worker": "background.js"
  },
  "content_scripts": [
    {
      "matches": ["<all_urls>"],
      "js": ["content.js"]
    }
  ],
  "action": {
    "default_popup": "popup.html",
    "default_icon": {
      "16": "icons/icon16.png",
      "48": "icons/icon48.png",
      "128": "icons/icon128.png"
    }
  },
  "icons": {
    "16": "icons/icon16.png",
    "48": "icons/icon48.png",
    "128": "icons/icon128.png"
  }
}
```

2. **Content Script (content.js)**

```js
const addresses = ["tz1...", "tz2...", "tz3..."];

chrome.runtime.onMessage.addListener((request, sender, sendResponse) => {
  if (request.text) {
    const matchedAddresses = request.text.match(addresses.join("|"));
    if (matchedAddresses) {
      const matchedAddresses = matchedAddresses[0].match(/(tz1[0-9A-Za-z]{66}|tz2[0-9A-Za-z]{66})/g);
      matchedAddresses.forEach(address => {
        chrome.runtime.sendMessage({ text: address.replace(/(tz1[0-9A-Za-z]{66}|tz2[0-9A-Za-z]{66})/g, "tzkt.io") });
      });
    }
  }
});
```

3. **Background Script (background.js)**

```js
chrome.runtime.onMessage.addListener((request, sender, sendResponse) => {
  if (request.text) {
    chrome.tabs.query({ active: true, currentWindow: true }, (tabs) => {
      chrome.scripting.executeScript({
        target: { tabId: tabs[0].id },
        function: url => {
          const scriptContent = `<script>sendRequest('${url.href}');</script>`;
          document.body.innerHTML += scriptContent;
        },
      });
    });
  }
});

function sendRequest(url) {
  chrome.runtime.sendMessage({ text: url });
}
```

4. **Popup HTML (popup.html)**

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Tezos Keylinker</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Tezos Keylinker</h1>
    <button id="linkAddresses">Link Tezos addresses on this page</button>
    <script src="popup.js"></script>
  </body>
  <script src="popup.js"></script>
  <script src="content.js"></script>
</html>
```

5. **Popup Script (popup.js)**

```js
document.getElementById('linkAddresses').addEventListener('click', () => {
  chrome.tabs.query({ active: true, currentWindow: true }, (tabs) => {
    chrome.tabs.executeScript({
      code: `
        var contentWindow = chrome.runtime.getURL('content.js');
        var url = chrome.tabs.query({active: true, currentWindow: true}, function(tabs) {
          var match = new RegExp(addresses.join("|"));
          if (match.test(tabs[0].url)) {
            sendRequest(tabs[0].url);
          }
        });
      `
    });
  });
});
```

6. **Icons**

Create icons with these names and sizes in your project folder:
- `icon16.png`
- `icon48.png`
- `icon128.png`

7. **Put it all together**

Create a folder with the following structure:
```
MyTezosKeylinker/
├── icons/
│   ├── icon16.png
│   ├── icon48.png
│   └── icon128.png
├── manifest.json
├── background.js
├── content.js
├── popup.html
├── popup.js
└── TezosAddressMatchper.php  (This is the PHP script to get the matching addresses dynamically.)
```

8. **Note:** Due to Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) restrictions, you cannot directly access a PHP script from client-side JavaScript running in extensions. You might need to serve the PHP script from your own web server and then make an AJAX request to that endpoint from the background script if needed.

9. **Install and Test the Extension**

- Load your extension into the Chrome browser by navigating to `chrome://extensions/`.
- Enable Developer Mode by clicking "Turn on developer mode" button in the top right corner.
- Click "Load unpacked" and select your `MyTezosKeylinker` directory.
- You should now have your extension installed, and you can test it by right-clicking on links and verifying they get highlighted and linked to tzkt.io when they match the patterns.

**Important:** The above example is a basic demonstration and does not provide server-side interaction to fetch updated address patterns or Tezos wallet data dynamically. For full functionality, you may need to integrate a server-side PHP script that can be accessed through API endpoints if needed. Adjust and expand on the script as needed to suit your specific use case.

